Hi All,

At wits end here so hoping someone can help.

When using an if statement to check if a personalisation token is equal to a string, it is consistently evaluating as false (even when it should be true).

Personalisation token is evaluating correctly as a string - and is a custom equation concatenating three strings from other properties. For example:

£1 - £1,000 - No - Vacuum

In the example below - when I use a contact that I know has the matching value, it still returns a "Not Match".

{% set type = personalization_token("contact.case_study_type") %}

{% if type == "£1 - £1,000 - No - Vacuum" %}
&lt;p&gt;Matched&lt;/p&gt;
{% else %}
&lt;p&gt;Not Match&lt;/p&gt;
{% endif %}

Any help much appreciated.

Hi <@U06US2S7RFU>
try this if-statement

```{% set type = contact.case_study_type %}

{% if type = "£1 - £1,000 - No - Vacuum" %}
&lt;p&gt;matched&lt;/p&gt;
{% else %}
&lt;p&gt;not matched&lt;/p&gt;
{% endif %}```
So basically just using the property itself, not the personalization_token

Also wondering if you're storing "£1 - £1,000 - No - Vacuum" as a string in the CRM or if it's a combination of several properties

Hey <@U077R95N3KJ>
are you building the Landing page in HubSpot or a different tool?
Might getting it wrong but if you're building the page in HubSpot - is there a reason why you don't use the "form" module?

If it's a different tool like wordpress, squarespace you'd like to embed the form in make sure that the embed code *does not* have the `css: ''` addition in the code so the form looks like this:
```&lt;script charset="utf-8" type="text/javascript" src="//js.hsforms.net/forms/embed/v2.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  hbspt.forms.create({
    region: "na1",
    portalId: "XXXXXXX",
    formId: "xxx-xxx-xxx-xxx"
  });
&lt;/script&gt;```

Also make sure that the "set as raw HTML" option is disabled(see screenshot)

